title: Reed named new director of SHESC
desc: Kaye Reed, Research Associate with IHO and President’s Professor will lead the School of Human Evolution and Social Change.

title: ASU professor named AAAS Fellow
desc: Gary Schwartz, who has devoted his career to unlocking the mysteries of human's unique life history through examining how our teeth grow, has been named a fellow of the American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS).

title: Using ‘baby’ teeth to predict hominin tooth size
desc: A new study by an international team including ASU researchers Gary Schwartz, Susanne Daly, and Kierstin Catlett, combined tools from embryology, comparative anatomy and computational biology to reveal that a single embryonic rule has regulated hominin tooth size.

title: Extinctions past/present discussed at Origins forum
desc: IHO Associate Director Curtis Marean joined Origins Project Director Lawrence Krauss and others on stage in the latest offering from the Great Debate series to discuss “Inconvenient Truths: From Love to Extinctions.”

title: Innovations less complex with access to more information
desc: IHO researchers Maxime Derex and Rob Boyd find that innovations are less complex when people have access to more information.

title: A diversity of passions
desc: ASU Foundation’s Impact magazine features IHO-affiliated graduate student Halszka Glowacka.

title: ASU archaeologist goes 'Jeep' into Mongolia
desc: When archaeologist Charles Perreault traveled to Mongolia for some investigative fieldwork, he didn’t bring the typical tool set of shovels and spades. Instead, he brought two all-terrain Jeeps, beginning a new project that will improve our knowledge of the early hominin groups that occupied northeast Asia, including ancient Homo sapiens, Neanderthals and a newly discovered species called Denisovans.

title: Past climate key to mammal communities today
desc: The distribution of species today may largely be a product of the climate of the deep past, or paleoclimate.
